<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN">
<html>
<head>
<title>Help: Using custom fonts in templates</title>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=iso-8859-1">
<link href="../style.css" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css">
</head>

<body>
<p class="titlebold">Using custom fonts in templates</p>
<p class="text">To add custom fonts, from the template editor choose File &gt; Add
  Custom Fonts...</p>
<p class="text">Simply upload a zip file of the fonts you wish to add. All fonts
  must be in PC Type 1 format. Each font will need two files: an outline and
  a metrics file. These pairs should be either afm&quot; and &quot;pfa&quot; files
  or a pair of &quot;pfm&quot; and &quot;pfb&quot; files. You will need to reload
  the template editor for your fonts to appear in the font menu.</p>
<p class="text"><strong>Note:</strong> Fonts must be appropriately licensed for
  your use before uploading them. You are responsible for the use of any copyrighted
  material
  used with the VariaPrint&#8482; system.</p>
</body>
</html>
